      "text": "Adjusted for inflation, the minimum wage peaked in 1968 at $8.54 (in 2014 dollars).[http://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2015/07/23/5-facts-about-the-minimum-wage/ 5 facts about the minimum wage] Progressives believe that stagnating wages perpetuate income inequality and that raising the minimum wage is a necessary step to combat inequality.<ref name=\":2\" /> If the minimum wage grew at the rate of productivity growth in the United States, it would be $21.72 an hour, nearly three times as much as the current $7.25 an hour.[http://cepr.net/documents/publications/min-wage1-2012-03.pdf The Minimum Wage is Too Damn Low] Popular progressives, such as Senator [[Bernie Sanders]] and Rep. [[Keith Ellison]], have endorsed a federally mandated wage increase to $15 an hour.[https://ourrevolution.com/issues/a-living-wage/ A Living Wage] The movement has already seen success with its implementation in California with the passing of bill to raise the minimum wage $1 every year until reaching $15 an hour in 2021.[https://ballotpedia.org/California_%22Fair_Wage_Act_of_2016%22_$15_Minimum_Wage_Initiative_(2016)#Senate_Bill_3 California] New York workers are lobbying for similar legislation as many continue to rally for a minimum wage increase as part of the Fight for $15 ([[Fast food worker strikes]]) movement.[http://fightfor15.org/ Fight for $15]"
